    "General-purpose formal languages such as Lean 31 still require a large amount of groundwork to describe most IMO geometry problems at present.",
    "We do not directly address this challenge as it requires deep expertise and substantial research outside the scope of theorem-proving methodologies.",
    "To sidestep this barrier, we instead adopted a more specialized language used in GEX 10, JGEX 17, MMP/ Geometer 13 and GeoLogic 19, a line of work that aims to provide a logical and graphical environment for synthetic geometry theorems with human-like non-degeneracy and topological assumptions.",
